1
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:34,720
<i>This bastard's one of your guys.</i>

2
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,640
His name's Chen.

3
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:39,440
He used to be a boxer.
He fought in China and got really famous.

4
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:42,280
Would you be interested
in putting some money on it, Mr. Wong?

5
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:44,880
<i>We need to take out Kluay first.</i>
<i>That's the only way to save those kids.</i>

6
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:46,640
If we move too fast and go off-plan,

7
00:01:46,720 --> 00:01:47,840
we'll all end up dead.

8
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,440
I knew your face looked familiar.

9
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:51,600
I'm friends with the guy
you beat half to death.

10
00:01:51,680 --> 00:01:54,720
<i>You said my friend</i>
<i>tried to rape your girl.</i>

11
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,760
<i>Let me tell you something.</i>

12
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:59,120
<i>-She wanted it.</i>
<i>-Don't listen to him.</i>

13
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:02,280
<i>Your girl Coco, she's just a call girl.</i>

14
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:04,160
An escort. You know that, right?

15
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:05,480
Why do we have to run?

16
00:02:05,560 --> 00:02:08,039
We didn't get the money,
and that bastard Kluay cheated us.

17
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,479
Excuse me, idiots.

18
00:02:09,560 --> 00:02:12,680
Are we going to wait for them
to figure it out and escape too late?

19
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:14,080
Talk in the car.

20
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:26,280
-Unchain!
-Unchain!

21
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,360
Looks like you're winning over the crowd.

22
00:02:29,720 --> 00:02:32,040
I don't know about the crowd.

23
00:02:32,920 --> 00:02:37,520
But you've completely won me over.

24
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:41,280
Unchain! Unchain! Unchain!

25
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:43,440
Hurry, let's go.

26
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:25,600
You crazy bastards!

27
00:03:27,320 --> 00:03:29,320
Go after them! Don't let them get away!

28
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,880
-Yes, boss.
-Move.

29
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,000
Catch them!

30
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:36,960
Move! Out of the way!

31
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:39,280
Stop!

32
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:42,120
Hurry! Run!

33
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,600
Where are they?

34
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:47,640
Did you find them?

35
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:48,680
No sign of them.

36
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:50,240
-Geez!
-Damn it!

37
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:52,640
So the money we got

38
00:03:52,720 --> 00:03:55,800
was totally random?
There was no plan at all?

39
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:57,520
Not exactly.

40
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,280
I already knew

41
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:01,760
he wouldn't let Chen throw the fight.

42
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,920
But the moment he locked eyes with Pae,

43
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,720
I knew immediately
that we had to go with this plan.

44
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,640
Am I right, Pae?

45
00:04:10,400 --> 00:04:12,240
Hey, give us a warning next time.

46
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:13,720
I almost had a heart attack.

47
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:15,760
Look, I didn't know the whole plan either

48
00:04:15,840 --> 00:04:18,480
until I went downstairs to get the bag
and switched it upstairs.

49
00:04:18,560 --> 00:04:19,800
You should've told me sooner.

50
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:22,880
I was afraid my acting
wouldn't be convincing, so I didn't dare.

51
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:24,920
Still, you handled it well,

52
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:28,280
getting Kluay worked up enough
to send someone back for the big cash.

53
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:34,800
But I hope those kids
can follow Admin's plan.

54
00:04:34,880 --> 00:04:36,680
The really impressive part

55
00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:41,160
was Admin's lucky ring.

56
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:43,720
This is a bet.
The money has to be on the table.

57
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:47,160
If it were you, Mr. Kluay,
you wouldn't be happy either.

58
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:51,560
<i>Go back and get all the money</i>
<i>from the safe at the boxing gym.</i>

59
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:53,880
-<i>Boss, isn't that money for Louis?</i>
-<i>Do it.</i>

60
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,320
He's sending someone back for the money.

61
00:05:46,520 --> 00:05:48,880
Wait. What about that thing?

62
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:51,920
Don't worry. Admin
already took care of it.

63
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,160
Thanks.

64
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:56,440
Honestly, we should be thanking
Angpao's equipment.

65
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,960
It got us all the evidence,
the CCTV footage,

66
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:00,400
and the audio recordings.

67
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:02,800
He's not getting away with this.

68
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,520
I hope so.

69
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:18,760
Boss, when I came in,
he was already unconscious.

70
00:06:18,840 --> 00:06:21,400
Boss!

71
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:26,400
What about the money
I was supposed to pay Louis?

72
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,600
It's gone, boss.

73
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:28,760
Huh?

74
00:06:28,840 --> 00:06:29,920
It's gone.

75
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:33,520
-Gone?
-I'm sorry, boss.

76
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:34,800
Damn it!

77
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:38,720
I'm sorry, boss.

78
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,360
Boss, don't!

79
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:45,120
Please don't shoot, boss! I'm sorry!
Give me another chance.

80
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,240
-Freeze!
-Drop your weapons!

81
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,360
-Drop your weapons!
-Put them down!

82
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:52,360
-Hands up!
-Get on the ground! Now!

83
00:06:53,520 --> 00:06:54,880
What's this, Officer?

84
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:57,640
Do you know who I am?
Bursting in here like this,

85
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,280
do you even have a search warrant?

86
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:01,280
I have an arrest warrant.

87
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:12,640
<i>Korkiat Sawangweerakorn, aka Boss Kluay,</i>
<i>a well-known boxing promoter,</i>

88
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,320
<i>is now a suspect in a case involving</i>

89
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:15,960
-<i>unlawful detention and alleged ties</i>
-Stay calm, kids.

90
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:18,560
-<i>to a human trafficking network.</i>
-It's okay. We're here to help.

91
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:22,120
<i>Police have rescued</i>

92
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:24,200
<i>more than 20 young victims</i>

93
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:28,680
<i>who were subjected to abuse</i>
<i>and forced into illegal labor.</i>

94
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:29,480
BOXING CAMP OWNER ARRESTED
IN HUMAN TRAFFICKING CASE

95
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:33,160
<i>Officials say the investigation</i>
<i>is expanding</i>

96
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:36,240
<i>to determine whether there are ties</i>
<i>to illegal loan networks.</i>

97
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:39,080
-Oh, that Boss Kluay.
-Done.

98
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,240
-He's finished.
-Game over.

99
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:42,280
-Everyone.
-Sit down.

100
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,200
-Everyone.
-Yeah?

101
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:46,560
Admin sent each of you two million.

102
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:47,800
Two million!

103
00:07:50,640 --> 00:07:51,680
Seriously?

104
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:53,080
-Two million. Here.
-Wow!

105
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:55,280
-Two million.
-Seriously?

106
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:59,520
And another one million
for Mr. Pae, our Mr. Wong.

107
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:03,280
Hope it makes it to him safely.

108
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:04,680
One million!

109
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:06,400
As for the rest of the money,

110
00:08:06,480 --> 00:08:09,040
Admin distributed it among the families
of the children who were taken.

111
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,200
Come here.

112
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,520
Wait, hold on.

113
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:20,400
How can we be sure Boss Kluay
won't beat the charges and come after us?

114
00:08:20,480 --> 00:08:21,920
Like I said before,

115
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:24,240
once he can't pay Louis,

116
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:27,160
Boss Kluay loses all his protection.

117
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:30,720
Forget a long prison sentence.

118
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,480
He might not even make it out alive.

119
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:35,120
-That bastard's got a lot of enemies.
-Game over.

120
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:37,440
Take that guy in too.

121
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:42,360
-Smells so good.
-Open it.

122
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,920
That knife's pretty cool.

123
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:04,600
Nice, right? I carved it myself.

124
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:06,600
Hey, open it.

125
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:10,080
-Hold on. I'll treat you to boat noodles.
-You said it.

126
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:11,320
Nice knife.

127
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:15,080
Where'd you get it? Can I have it?

128
00:09:15,160 --> 00:09:17,560
No. My dad gave it to me.

129
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,760
Ris, let's go.

130
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:34,960
Come on.

131
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:40,520
Wow, that's a lot of money.

132
00:10:03,760 --> 00:10:06,640
Louis! You came to help me, right?

133
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:11,960
The lawyer is standing right here.

134
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,640
How did this happen?

135
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:18,920
I've never missed a payment. You said
you could take care of everything.

136
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:20,760
So why am I still under arrest?

137
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:25,760
Calm down, boss.

138
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,600
Things are changing right now.

139
00:10:27,680 --> 00:10:31,200
The old big shot retired,
and a new one took his place.

140
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:34,080
The only problem is

141
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:36,360
I haven't been able to buy off
the new guy yet.

142
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,520
It's that Big Tum guy, right?

143
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:45,560
Let's get back to business, boss.

144
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:48,680
Where's this month's payment?

145
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:52,520
I wasn't trying to stiff you.

146
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:55,040
I got scammed.

147
00:10:58,920 --> 00:11:00,000
Boss,

148
00:11:00,080 --> 00:11:03,880
do you know how much dirt is coming out

149
00:11:03,960 --> 00:11:05,560
about your business right now?

150
00:11:05,640 --> 00:11:08,440
And the cops just keep digging.

151
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:11,120
If this keeps up,

152
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,640
I'm afraid…

153
00:11:12,720 --> 00:11:14,240
Louis!

154
00:11:14,320 --> 00:11:16,200
Please, just get me out first.

155
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:18,880
Whatever you want, I'll pay any amount.

156
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:21,320
Please. I'm begging you.

157
00:11:21,400 --> 00:11:24,480
Louis, help me. Name your price.

158
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:29,480
Fine, boss.

159
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:32,280
In that case,
I'll take care of your problem first.

160
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:34,880
-See you around.
-Thank you so much.

161
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:42,080
Once he's transferred to detention,

162
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:45,560
finish him off.

163
00:11:48,760 --> 00:11:50,040
See you around, boss.

164
00:11:57,400 --> 00:12:01,960
Whoa, Koh. This is amazing. It's gorgeous.

165
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:04,240
Sis Hong is really something, huh?

166
00:12:04,320 --> 00:12:07,240
Just the other day, she wanted to kill us.

167
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:09,520
And now she's inviting us on a trip.

168
00:12:10,720 --> 00:12:13,440
What kind of joke is fate playing on us?

169
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:15,480
Oh, right. Speaking of fate,

170
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:19,880
what are we doing about Admin?
Are we taking those jobs or not?

171
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:26,360
Koh!

172
00:12:27,600 --> 00:12:28,760
What's with you?

173
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,360
Hey.

174
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:37,920
Don't tell me you like Risa.

175
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,440
Are you crazy?

176
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:46,760
Do you remember Aek,
the guy I've been looking for?

177
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:48,080
Of course I do.

178
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:55,160
I think Risa is his daughter.

179
00:12:58,160 --> 00:13:00,760
How do you know? Are you sure?

180
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:04,200
So what are you going to do?

181
00:13:04,280 --> 00:13:07,520
Are you going to tell Risa
that you knew her father?

182
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:27,360
What are you doing out here by yourself?

183
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:31,360
Just thinking.

184
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:35,480
About your dad, right?

185
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:41,040
Don't act like you know everything.

186
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:50,400
Honestly,

187
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:53,800
there are still two things bothering me.

188
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,080
First,

189
00:13:56,880 --> 00:13:59,400
I want to know if he's still alive.

190
00:14:01,280 --> 00:14:03,040
If he's dead,

191
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:07,160
then I can stop waiting like this.

192
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:11,480
If he's still alive, what will you do?

193
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:14,120
I guess…

194
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:21,440
I don't know.

195
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:24,040
I'd probably ask him

196
00:14:27,360 --> 00:14:28,680
why he left me behind back then.

197
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:36,800
And the other thing?

198
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:42,720
I want to know

199
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:45,520
that day at the train station…

200
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:50,600
<i>I'm sure</i>

201
00:14:51,240 --> 00:14:54,880
<i>he saw the train leaving.</i>

202
00:14:56,080 --> 00:14:59,520
He heard me calling out to him.

203
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:04,200
<i>But how could he</i>

204
00:15:04,760 --> 00:15:06,960
bring himself to leave me behind?

205
00:15:20,760 --> 00:15:24,360
Then I hope he's still alive.

206
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:29,800
So you can keep hoping
to find that answer.

207
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:56,560
FIVE YEARS AGO

208
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:58,680
Split up and search. Go!

209
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:01,960
I promise.

210
00:16:02,040 --> 00:16:04,840
Soon our lives are going to get better.

211
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,200
Yes.

212
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:18,000
Can you manage? We have to go.

213
00:16:25,480 --> 00:16:26,560
Didn't find him?

214
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:28,160
-No.
-Okay.

215
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:30,200
You check down here. I'll check the train.

216
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:32,440
Come on. Follow me.

217
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,880
I'll go get you some painkillers.

218
00:16:41,600 --> 00:16:44,040
-Okay.
-I have something for you.

219
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:48,120
I made this knife myself.

220
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,480
Here. I want you to keep it.

221
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:56,640
Wait here for me. I'll be right back.

222
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,800
I have to take you to talk to him.

223
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,400
Don't run, Aek.

224
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,400
His men are looking for you everywhere.

225
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:27,599
There's no way you're getting away.

226
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:31,320
But if I go back with you,
I'm dead either way.

227
00:17:33,480 --> 00:17:34,720
Just let me go.

228
00:17:35,840 --> 00:17:37,600
I don't think you have a choice.

229
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:44,080
<i>Express Train No. 109</i>

230
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:47,720
<i>is now departing Bangkok Station.</i>
<i>Thank you.</i>

231
00:17:58,760 --> 00:18:01,280
Dad!

232
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:06,800
Dad!

233
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:09,520
Dad!

234
00:18:33,600 --> 00:18:38,000
You got this dressed up just to go eat?

235
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:42,200
Well, I didn't know
what kind of place she was taking us to.

236
00:18:42,280 --> 00:18:45,480
She said to dress nicely,
so I dressed up just in case.

237
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:48,720
What? Is it too much?

238
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,640
Not at all!

239
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:59,280
Wow, sis!

240
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:02,960
You even bought a new outfit for this?

241
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:05,480
I'm telling you,
the place I'm taking you to

242
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:07,920
is super premium.

243
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,200
Getting those vouchers was a battle.

244
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:13,280
Otherwise, I wouldn't have had Gao
book a table in advance.

245
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:17,160
Wait a second.
A premium place with vouchers?

246
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:20,840
Excuse me. Even though it's a buffet,

247
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,480
it's almost 2,000 baht per person.

248
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:25,720
Most importantly,
the deal is amazing, four for three.

249
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:27,000
There are eight of us,

250
00:19:27,080 --> 00:19:29,800
so we only need six vouchers.
It's perfect!

251
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,240
Can we go now, sis?

252
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:35,360
I can't wait for the free food.

253
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:38,640
Go ahead then. What about Koh and Chen?

254
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:41,960
I asked them,
but they were too lazy. Let them be.

255
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:45,200
Such a waste of a good deal.
Come on, let's go.

256
00:19:52,240 --> 00:19:55,880
<i>What is it, Gao? Is the place packed?</i>

257
00:19:55,960 --> 00:20:00,320
Packed with what, Hong? I'm looking
right at it. There's not a soul here.

258
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:05,120
Good. We won't have to fight for food.

259
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,480
Feels like we booked out the whole place.

260
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:08,520
<i>That's nice.</i>

261
00:20:08,600 --> 00:20:10,680
Yeah, the whole place.

262
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:12,520
The place is closed.

263
00:20:12,600 --> 00:20:14,840
<i>The restaurant went out of business!</i>

264
00:20:14,920 --> 00:20:15,800
Here.

265
00:20:16,560 --> 00:20:18,480
Is this some kind of joke?

266
00:20:18,560 --> 00:20:20,560
It normally costs 2,000 baht per person.

267
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:22,280
-But they sold it to us for 200.
-Yeah.

268
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:23,880
How could it be that cheap?

269
00:20:23,960 --> 00:20:25,520
<i>Are you kidding me?</i>

270
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:26,640
What do you mean?

271
00:20:26,720 --> 00:20:29,200
Hong, it means the restaurant…

272
00:20:29,280 --> 00:20:31,920
It means people are fooling you.

273
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,400
It means you got scammed.

274
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:36,120
<i>Sis, I'm telling you.</i>

275
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:38,760
If it's cheap and looks
too good to be true, it probably is!

276
00:20:42,760 --> 00:20:45,200
-Was it a scam, sis?
-Yeah.

277
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:49,480
I bought almost the entire booklet.
Spent nearly 30,000 baht.

278
00:20:49,560 --> 00:20:52,360
I knew it, sis.
Haven't you been watching the news?

279
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:54,440
Scams like this are everywhere these days.

280
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:58,360
Small investment, huge returns.
Classic pyramid scheme.

281
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,720
Oh no. I got dressed up for nothing.

282
00:21:01,800 --> 00:21:04,320
No fancy free meal after all.

283
00:21:04,400 --> 00:21:05,760
Hey, don't worry.

284
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:10,200
A woman like me keeps her word.
If I said I'm treating, I'm treating.

285
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:13,800
Let's go. Which floor
is the restaurant on?

286
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:17,320
RESTAURANT 2 FL
M POWER GROUP SEMINAR BY YOLLADA ARAYASAI

287
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:19,400
There. Second floor.

288
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:22,160
Why don't you get it?

289
00:21:22,240 --> 00:21:25,400
If you keep being this careless,
I won't pass your probation. Got it?

290
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:28,920
I'm truly sorry. This won't happen again.

291
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:31,400
Fix it before I get back.

292
00:21:38,920 --> 00:21:41,320
M POWER GROUP SEMINAR BY YOLLADA ARAYASAI

293
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:46,200
Call the others back to eat at the hotel.

294
00:21:46,280 --> 00:21:48,360
Risa, you're coming with me.

295
00:21:58,760 --> 00:21:59,960
Hello there.

296
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:03,280
My secretary and I are here
to check in our seminar guests early.

297
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:05,120
How many VIP rooms do we need?

298
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,600
Eight VIP rooms.

299
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:13,800
Alright. We'll take
the hotel buffet promo too.

300
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:15,800
May I have the reservation name?

301
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:19,800
What? You don't know me?

302
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:23,320
I'm Yollada, owner of M Power.

303
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:26,000
We're hosting the seminar here tomorrow.

304
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,520
Oh, yes.

305
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:30,840
May I see your ID, please?

306
00:22:30,920 --> 00:22:34,000
Listen. I've traveled all this way.

307
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:36,000
Can we not make this so complicated?

308
00:22:36,080 --> 00:22:37,680
But…

309
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:39,360
You just started working here, right?

310
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:41,560
Go get the manager
who scolded you earlier.

311
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:44,160
Alright, no problem. I'll handle it.

312
00:22:44,240 --> 00:22:47,080
Give me the buffet vouchers too.
I'm starving.

313
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:48,480
Sure.

314
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:52,120
There are three right now.

315
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:56,160
I'll get more. Please wait a moment.

316
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:03,280
I thought you said you'd treat us?

317
00:23:05,160 --> 00:23:07,960
I said I'd treat you.
I didn't say I'd pay for everything.

318
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,840
Miss Yollada, you've aged quite a bit.

319
00:23:16,480 --> 00:23:18,760
Excuse me. Were you talking
to me just now?

320
00:23:20,680 --> 00:23:23,760
Besides the wrinkles,
you've also got a hearing problem.

321
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:42,920
It's been a long time, Hong.

322
00:23:44,320 --> 00:23:45,840
Don't be mad at me.

323
00:23:46,960 --> 00:23:49,120
The world's just cruel like this, Hong.

324
00:23:53,320 --> 00:23:57,160
I thought you were dead.
You're really tough.

325
00:23:58,600 --> 00:24:00,760
-I will kill you!
-Ms. Mam!

326
00:24:01,680 --> 00:24:03,400
Hello, Ms. Mam!

327
00:24:03,480 --> 00:24:05,560
Why didn't you tell me you were coming?

328
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,160
Just a little change of plan.

329
00:24:07,760 --> 00:24:10,160
I wanted to check out the seminar venue.

330
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:14,240
In that case, I'll open the room for you,
then show you the seminar hall.

331
00:24:14,840 --> 00:24:16,200
Thank you.

332
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:20,680
The rooms are ready, Ms. Yollada.

333
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:23,840
And here are five more

334
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:25,320
restaurant vouchers.

335
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:34,800
Let us back in.

336
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:36,160
Why are you pushing us?

337
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:38,640
Why are you pushing us?

338
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:40,600
-Can you treat guests with some manners?
-Sis, careful!

339
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:42,200
-You guys.
-I'll call Kanchai!

340
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:43,880
-Call him!
-We'll go on Riding The Trend.

341
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:45,160
-Call him!
-Don't.

342
00:24:45,240 --> 00:24:46,200
You'd better get ready.

343
00:24:46,280 --> 00:24:48,840
Prepare a gift basket
and apologize properly.

344
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:51,400
Call him, Yak!

345
00:24:51,480 --> 00:24:54,320
-If you don't stop me, I'm charging in.
-Enough.

346
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:55,560
And I mean what I say.

347
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:58,680
If they don't welcome us,
we won't use their service.

348
00:24:58,760 --> 00:25:02,040
Enough already. You're wasting their time.
Look how many people are here.

349
00:25:03,040 --> 00:25:05,760
You tried to sneak in for a free meal
and used someone else's name.

350
00:25:05,840 --> 00:25:07,800
The hotel's already kind enough
not to call the cops.

351
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:10,320
-Let them call the cops!
-Yeah, exactly.

352
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:12,320
Hong, I know what kind of person you are.

353
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:14,240
Can you stop scamming people all the time?

354
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:16,640
-I'll smack your mouth, kid.
-I'm just telling the truth.

355
00:25:17,480 --> 00:25:21,560
Hong, don't overthink it.

356
00:25:21,640 --> 00:25:24,640
Let's eat somewhere simple around here.
There are plenty of places.

357
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:26,840
Yeah. If they don't welcome us,
then we'll…

358
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:31,400
Hey, Gao, does this woman look familiar?
Have we seen her before?

359
00:25:32,440 --> 00:25:33,440
That damn Mam!

360
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:37,080
The one who betrayed us 13 years ago!

361
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:40,000
YOLLADA ARAYASAI, M POWER

362
00:25:51,880 --> 00:25:54,440
NEW MISSION
BRIEFING TOMORROW AT 10 A.M.

363
00:26:08,480 --> 00:26:10,880
<i>You've contacted all of them, right?</i>

364
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:13,640
Yes, I have. They're on their way.

365
00:26:13,720 --> 00:26:17,640
<i>The details of the operation</i>
<i>are in the document I sent you.</i>

366
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:18,720
<i>Make sure to pass it on.</i>

367
00:26:18,800 --> 00:26:20,720
-Understood.
-<i>Any other questions?</i>

368
00:26:22,520 --> 00:26:25,640
Yes. Why did you choose
these eight people?

369
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:28,120
They don't seem
to work well together at all.

370
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:30,440
And they look like con artists

371
00:26:30,520 --> 00:26:32,040
you can't trust.

372
00:26:33,800 --> 00:26:35,280
<i>Everyone in this world</i>

373
00:26:35,360 --> 00:26:38,040
<i>is a con artist in some way.</i>

374
00:26:38,960 --> 00:26:42,040
<i>Me, you, anyone.</i>

375
00:26:43,080 --> 00:26:45,880
<i>We all live with lies</i>

376
00:26:45,960 --> 00:26:48,280
<i>and keep deceiving each other.</i>

377
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:52,560
<i>Society may brand them as con artists</i>

378
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:54,560
<i>full of tricks</i>

379
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:58,360
<i>and deceit. But to me,</i>

380
00:26:58,440 --> 00:27:02,760
<i>each of them is honest</i>
<i>about their own feelings.</i>

381
00:27:03,280 --> 00:27:05,080
<i>They're the most trustworthy people.</i>

382
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:32,920
<i>It's good to see you all again.</i>

383
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:36,480
<i>Since we're meeting again, that means</i>

384
00:27:36,560 --> 00:27:41,240
<i>you want to be part of this game of mine.</i>

385
00:27:41,840 --> 00:27:44,000
<i>The terms are the same.</i>

386
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:47,560
<i>You must complete</i>
<i>the missions assigned to you.</i>

387
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:51,840
<i>Your payment will be handed out</i>
<i>after the mission is complete.</i>

388
00:27:51,920 --> 00:27:55,240
<i>Your new mission this time</i>

389
00:27:55,760 --> 00:27:58,000
<i>is taking down a pyramid scheme.</i>

390
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:04,080
This Admin guy is pretty weird, huh?

391
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:08,000
Covered from head to toe, like a character
from a Japanese cartoon, don't you think?

392
00:28:10,040 --> 00:28:11,680
-Chen!
-What?

393
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:13,200
What are you doing?

394
00:28:13,280 --> 00:28:16,160
Can't you see? I'm taking notes.
Last time, Admin talked forever.

395
00:28:16,240 --> 00:28:19,320
I couldn't keep up, so I got lost.

396
00:28:20,720 --> 00:28:24,440
<i>A pyramid scheme lures people</i>
<i>into investing in a network.</i>

397
00:28:24,520 --> 00:28:27,960
<i>It often promises high returns</i>

398
00:28:28,040 --> 00:28:31,320
<i>in a short time, but in reality,</i>

399
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:32,560
<i>there's no real investment.</i>

400
00:28:32,640 --> 00:28:35,760
<i>The money from new members is used</i>

401
00:28:35,840 --> 00:28:37,880
<i>to pay earlier members.</i>

402
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:41,320
<i>When they can't get new members to invest,</i>

403
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:43,480
<i>the cycle collapses.</i>

404
00:28:43,560 --> 00:28:45,640
<i>The scheme eventually falls apart.</i>

405
00:28:45,720 --> 00:28:47,960
-Ms. Lin.
-Yes? What is it?

406
00:28:50,640 --> 00:28:54,640
Could you play the clip again?
I couldn't keep up, so I didn't get it.

407
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:56,440
Chen!

408
00:28:57,520 --> 00:29:00,120
He was just explaining.
Weren't you listening?

409
00:29:00,200 --> 00:29:02,600
Chen, I can explain it to you.

410
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:04,160
Great.

411
00:29:04,920 --> 00:29:07,280
The principle of a pyramid scheme

412
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:09,040
is recruiting more members.

413
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:11,040
Say I own this scheme.

414
00:29:11,120 --> 00:29:13,800
I invite Chen to invest two baht with me

415
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:16,800
and promise to pay him back
one baht every round.

416
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:18,560
Two baht, one baht.

417
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:21,080
Then Chen believes me
and gives me the money.

418
00:29:27,200 --> 00:29:28,280
Two baht now!

419
00:29:28,360 --> 00:29:32,560
Then I go trick Angpao
into investing the same way.

420
00:29:33,240 --> 00:29:37,320
I simply use Angpao's money
to pay Chen back.

421
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:42,920
Nice trick.

422
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:45,520
Once Chen sees he really got paid,

423
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:47,280
he invites Koh to invest too.

424
00:29:47,360 --> 00:29:49,600
Koh, join me. You'll make money.

425
00:29:51,480 --> 00:29:53,600
Then I use Koh's money

426
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:56,440
to pay Angpao back.

427
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:58,640
That's the pyramid cycle.

428
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:05,320
See? My money grows fast

429
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:06,840
without me investing anything at all.

430
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:10,280
Invest two, get one back.
By the third round, you're in profit.

431
00:30:10,360 --> 00:30:14,920
If I were playing, I wouldn't
put in one baht. I'd put in thousands.

432
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,160
Exactly.

433
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:20,640
Most people see that the returns
are worth the investment.

434
00:30:20,720 --> 00:30:24,680
Greed takes over. They borrow money,
hoping for a big payout.

435
00:30:28,840 --> 00:30:29,800
Look at that.

436
00:30:29,880 --> 00:30:31,000
Your return.

437
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:32,760
Thanks, kid.

438
00:30:32,840 --> 00:30:34,000
But once I can't find

439
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:37,280
any more members, I won't have the money
to keep the scheme going.

440
00:30:37,360 --> 00:30:38,320
Then everything ends.

441
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:42,360
I just scoop up all the money,
put it in my pocket,

442
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:46,440
and flee to a visa-free country.
Do you understand now, Chen?

443
00:30:46,520 --> 00:30:48,200
Crystal clear.

444
00:30:48,280 --> 00:30:51,080
Now that you understand,
can I have my money back?

445
00:30:51,160 --> 00:30:52,840
-Oh, right.
-Yak, where's the money?

446
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:55,400
-Where did it go? It's here.
-Right there.

447
00:30:55,480 --> 00:30:56,320
I can see it.

448
00:30:56,400 --> 00:30:59,600
Mungkorn, I thought
you could keep making money appear.

449
00:30:59,680 --> 00:31:01,080
Okay, alright.

450
00:31:01,680 --> 00:31:04,800
Now that everyone's clear,

451
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:06,960
let's look at the target for this mission.

452
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:12,760
That's…

453
00:31:16,560 --> 00:31:19,600
Her name is Mam Yollada Arayasai,

454
00:31:19,680 --> 00:31:23,480
owner of M Power Group,
an investment company on the surface,

455
00:31:23,560 --> 00:31:27,320
but in reality, it's a pyramid scheme.

456
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:38,520
Our apologies again

457
00:31:38,600 --> 00:31:41,080
for letting someone
impersonate you like that, Ms. Mam.

458
00:31:41,160 --> 00:31:43,680
It's fine. I don't mind.

459
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:45,880
But you should be careful.

460
00:31:45,960 --> 00:31:47,960
There are a lot of scammers around
these days.

461
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:49,560
<i>Thank you very much.</i>

462
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:54,160
<i>Next time, we hope you'll host</i>
<i>another seminar at our hotel.</i>

463
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:01,040
Gladly.

464
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:06,560
Mam!

465
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:08,320
You filthy liar!

466
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:11,280
You fraud!

467
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:14,960
Stay still!

468
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:19,040
-Let me go!
-Security! Help!

469
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:20,440
-Security!
-Security!

470
00:32:20,520 --> 00:32:22,240
-Please help!
-Remember this!

471
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:23,840
I'll expose every rotten thing
you've done!

472
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:25,560
I'll make sure you all rot in prison!

473
00:32:25,640 --> 00:32:27,560
You fake company! You lying frauds!

474
00:32:27,640 --> 00:32:29,040
-Move!
-Let me go!

475
00:32:29,120 --> 00:32:31,800
-Move! Get up!
-Let me go! I said let me go!

476
00:32:33,640 --> 00:32:35,880
This is already
the third incident this year.

477
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:38,880
If someone like this shows up
at next month's fundraising,

478
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:41,160
our company's reputation
will take an even bigger hit.

479
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:44,320
Maybe it's time

480
00:32:44,400 --> 00:32:47,040
to shut the company down like last time.

481
00:32:51,240 --> 00:32:52,080
Ms. Mam.

482
00:32:52,160 --> 00:32:54,160
Do you think starting a new company

483
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:55,840
is something you can do easily?

484
00:32:57,280 --> 00:33:00,600
Anyway, the fundraising
next month must go on.

485
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:11,120
Listen, Peter. You need to find
new high-end investors

486
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:13,480
so the system can keep running.

487
00:33:20,640 --> 00:33:22,840
It's the only way for us to survive.

488
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:24,640
Don't let me down.

489
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:28,040
I understand, Ms. Mam.

490
00:33:30,440 --> 00:33:31,880
As for that downline,

491
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:34,680
I don't ever want to see him again.

492
00:33:37,600 --> 00:33:38,640
Yes, ma'am.

493
00:33:50,440 --> 00:33:51,920
What happened between you and Mam?

494
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:55,760
Why do you resent her that much?

495
00:33:59,400 --> 00:34:01,600
Knowing that won't have anything
to do with the mission.

496
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:03,320
How is it not related?

497
00:34:04,520 --> 00:34:07,160
If you don't tell us about Mam,

498
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:11,000
how are we supposed to know
how to deal with her?

499
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:17,760
Mam and I used to be really close.

500
00:34:17,840 --> 00:34:20,280
I'd known her since she was young.

501
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,960
I loved her like my own little sister.

502
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:24,000
Until 13 years ago…

503
00:34:24,600 --> 00:34:26,360
<i>The latest reports show 13,000 victims</i>

504
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:29,440
<i>of the Kamnan Chang scheme</i>
<i>have now filed police complaints.</i>

505
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:32,600
<i>Total damages are estimated</i>
<i>at no less than three billion baht.</i>

506
00:34:32,679 --> 00:34:35,159
<i>This case may become</i>
<i>the worst pyramid scheme case</i>

507
00:34:35,239 --> 00:34:38,440
<i>in Thai history.</i>

508
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:47,000
Hong, what am I going to do?

509
00:34:47,080 --> 00:34:49,639
I don't want to go to prison.

510
00:34:49,719 --> 00:34:53,000
If Chang gets arrested,

511
00:34:53,080 --> 00:34:55,159
I'm going down with him for sure.

512
00:34:57,200 --> 00:35:00,480
Hey. Calm down.
Pull yourself together first.

513
00:35:01,360 --> 00:35:03,960
Hong, you have to help Chang

514
00:35:04,040 --> 00:35:07,920
get out of the house
before the police raid it. Please.

515
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:11,760
Hong, tell me how much you want.

516
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:14,040
I'll have Chang pay you
as much as you want.

517
00:35:14,120 --> 00:35:16,360
Mam, money isn't the problem.

518
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:18,960
You're my sister.
Of course, I'll help you.

519
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:22,480
How are you going to help?
I don't want to go to prison.

520
00:35:22,560 --> 00:35:24,080
-I don't want to get arrested.
-Can you calm down?

521
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:26,840
Get a grip. Can you be quiet for a second?
Let me think.

522
00:35:35,800 --> 00:35:36,960
I've got it.

523
00:35:37,720 --> 00:35:38,920
Got what?

524
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:43,000
Call Kamnan Chang.

525
00:35:43,080 --> 00:35:45,160
Tell him to burn down his own house.

526
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:47,440
What?

527
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:55,000
-Hurry up!
-He's in bad shape!

528
00:35:55,080 --> 00:35:56,240
Did you find Kamnan Chang?

529
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:59,120
Not yet. Just the gardener and maids
trapped in the back.

530
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:00,960
-Check them carefully.
-Yes.

531
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:06,840
Not him, sir.

532
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:10,760
Sir, he's in critical condition.

533
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:13,320
We need to get him
to the hospital immediately. Sergeant.

534
00:36:13,400 --> 00:36:14,640
-Help me out.
-Yes.

535
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:16,360
Take him to the ambulance now.

536
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:18,000
Whoa, he's in really bad shape.

537
00:36:18,080 --> 00:36:19,440
The ambulance is here!

538
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:22,960
-Open the door.
-Yes, sir! I'm here!

539
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:25,360
-Hurry up!
-I'll open the door.

540
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:27,160
I'll take care of him.

541
00:36:27,240 --> 00:36:31,000
Go on, do your work. Bye!

542
00:36:35,680 --> 00:36:37,160
Take it easy, will you?

543
00:36:37,240 --> 00:36:39,480
Gao! Why are you treating
the client like this?

544
00:36:39,560 --> 00:36:43,120
The client is king! If you treat him
like this, will he ever come back?

545
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:46,280
This suit already weighs ten kilos.
He can walk. Why dump his weight on me?

546
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:49,040
Take it off if it's heavy.
Let's get moving.

547
00:36:50,400 --> 00:36:52,800
Stop arguing. We need to switch vehicles

548
00:36:52,880 --> 00:36:54,800
-and move the money from the warehouse.
-Yes.

549
00:36:54,880 --> 00:36:56,240
Yes, ma'am.

550
00:37:03,680 --> 00:37:07,720
Wow, this is even more
than what the news reported.

551
00:37:11,440 --> 00:37:14,680
Your wages are all in this one bag.

552
00:37:14,760 --> 00:37:15,720
Don't get greedy!

553
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:19,560
What's so funny?

554
00:37:19,640 --> 00:37:22,800
You, Kamnan. You're funny.

555
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:26,880
I've never seen a greedy person
teach others not to be greedy.

556
00:37:28,400 --> 00:37:30,520
I've moved the money out safely, Mam.

557
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:32,440
See you at the gas station in 20 minutes.

558
00:37:32,520 --> 00:37:36,320
<i>Thanks so much, Hong.</i>
<i>I'd be screwed without you.</i>

559
00:37:37,960 --> 00:37:40,160
Let's go, Chang. Guys, get in the van.

560
00:37:40,240 --> 00:37:42,600
-Is there even a seat left?
-Hold on!

561
00:37:43,320 --> 00:37:45,160
I don't trust these two.

562
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:49,360
Hong, come with me. Just the two of us.

563
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:52,520
I don't trust you either.
Are you planning to betray us?

564
00:37:52,600 --> 00:37:53,760
Wait.

565
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:57,160
Just do what he says.
Let's get in the van.

566
00:37:57,240 --> 00:37:58,240
Hong.

567
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:02,000
-Wait, Hong.
-What?

568
00:38:02,080 --> 00:38:03,680
Can we trust Kamnan Chang?

569
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:07,920
Don't worry. I told you
Mam is trustworthy.

570
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:09,400
Alright, I'm off.

571
00:38:12,080 --> 00:38:13,080
Be careful.

572
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:15,840
I'm worried about her, Gao.

573
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:43,280
How's it going, Mam?
Told you not to worry.

574
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:44,520
I've got this.

575
00:38:54,160 --> 00:38:55,560
What is this, Mam?

576
00:38:58,400 --> 00:39:02,120
You fools! You really thought

577
00:39:02,200 --> 00:39:04,520
I'd share the money I earned?

578
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:12,720
Damn you, Mam!

579
00:39:16,440 --> 00:39:19,000
I practically earned this money myself.
You're the one

580
00:39:19,080 --> 00:39:20,560
who has no right to any of it.

581
00:39:20,640 --> 00:39:23,000
Mam. What are you doing?

582
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:29,200
Don't be mad at me. And thank you so much

583
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:31,080
for always helping me.

584
00:39:32,640 --> 00:39:34,080
How can you do this to me?

585
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:36,600
The world's just cruel like this, Hong.

586
00:39:43,720 --> 00:39:49,000
Wait. You got shot like that and survived?
How are you still alive?

587
00:39:50,320 --> 00:39:51,720
Because of greed.

588
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:55,880
What should we do
with these bodies, Ms. Mam?

589
00:39:56,520 --> 00:40:00,520
Leave them. Just take care of the car.

590
00:40:00,600 --> 00:40:01,560
Yes.

591
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:31,680
<i>If that day I hadn't stolen Mam's money,</i>

592
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:34,120
I probably wouldn't have survived
to see today.

593
00:40:37,160 --> 00:40:39,720
I really have to thank my greed that day.

594
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:45,160
But a loved one turning into an enemy

595
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:47,800
is also because of greed.

596
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:50,360
But I understand you.

597
00:40:50,440 --> 00:40:53,120
When someone you love betrays you,

598
00:40:53,760 --> 00:40:55,320
I'd be just as furious.

599
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:05,440
That's why I've been waiting
for the day to get back at her.

600
00:41:05,520 --> 00:41:06,880
That damn Mam.

601
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:15,040
The son of a major construction tycoon
in the Northeast. His name is Peak.

602
00:41:17,320 --> 00:41:19,360
The other day, he contacted me,

603
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:21,440
saying he's interested in investing.

604
00:41:21,520 --> 00:41:24,000
I checked his background.
He seems promising,

605
00:41:24,920 --> 00:41:26,960
so I set up a meeting with you.

606
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:30,760
"Young, ambitious newcomer
in the startup world."

607
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:36,200
His background looks solid.
Great job, Peter.

608
00:41:36,800 --> 00:41:40,240
<i>According to our info,</i>
<i>Mam is a lonely woman</i>

609
00:41:40,320 --> 00:41:42,040
who likes young guys.

610
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:43,960
So first,

611
00:41:44,040 --> 00:41:46,760
we need to send the person
who best fits her type

612
00:41:46,840 --> 00:41:47,920
to win her over

613
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:50,360
and get access to her money.

614
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:51,960
That means

615
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:56,040
we need someone handsome
and fresh, just her type.

616
00:41:56,120 --> 00:41:57,760
Then it'll be much easier

617
00:41:57,840 --> 00:41:59,040
to fool Mam.

618
00:42:04,040 --> 00:42:05,560
I guess it's me for the job.

619
00:42:09,240 --> 00:42:11,600
I meant Mungkorn.

620
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:21,360
Broken face, doctor no pick and sew!

621
00:42:24,720 --> 00:42:25,760
What does that mean?

622
00:42:25,840 --> 00:42:29,560
It means he's made a fool of himself.
No doctor can fix it!

623
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:33,480
Speaking Thai is funnier.

624
00:42:33,560 --> 00:42:35,120
Really? Alright, okay.

625
00:42:40,520 --> 00:42:44,400
-Have you reserved a table?
-Yes, table three.

626
00:42:44,480 --> 00:42:45,800
Right this way, please.

627
00:42:50,040 --> 00:42:51,160
Mam is inside the restaurant.

628
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:02,600
Is this Peak?

629
00:43:04,520 --> 00:43:05,360
Yes.

630
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:09,680
-Well, Ms. Mam?
-Yes.

631
00:43:11,120 --> 00:43:11,960
Please, have a seat.

632
00:43:18,880 --> 00:43:21,000
-Excuse me. Can we get the menu?
-Yes, of course.

633
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:25,800
-Was traffic bad?
-Not too much.

634
00:43:28,560 --> 00:43:33,040
Wait. How does disguising
as a rising startup star to flirt with Mam

635
00:43:33,120 --> 00:43:35,680
have anything to do
with taking down the pyramid scheme?

636
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:38,080
Because her company
is having cash flow problems.

637
00:43:38,800 --> 00:43:41,160
She needs a big investor to put money in.

638
00:43:42,040 --> 00:43:43,520
SAVINGS ACCOUNT, SCAN TO PAY

639
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:47,400
AMOUNT 1,200 BAHT

640
00:43:50,640 --> 00:43:52,160
I can't believe it.

641
00:43:52,240 --> 00:43:54,080
You're so young,

642
00:43:54,160 --> 00:43:57,440
yet you already own a series-A startup.

643
00:43:57,520 --> 00:44:00,920
You're even younger

644
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:03,680
and more beautiful than I imagined.

645
00:44:06,760 --> 00:44:09,240
Do you talk this sweetly to every woman?

646
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:14,880
Not at all. I just say what I see

647
00:44:14,960 --> 00:44:16,680
and feel.

648
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:21,080
Excuse me.

649
00:44:21,160 --> 00:44:24,120
May I bring the bill?
The restaurant is about to close.

650
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:25,280
Sure.

651
00:44:27,480 --> 00:44:29,960
So who should pay for this meal?

652
00:44:33,960 --> 00:44:36,560
Oh, I can pay this time.

653
00:44:37,360 --> 00:44:38,200
I'm just kidding.

654
00:44:57,200 --> 00:45:00,680
I think it's better to let the one

655
00:45:00,760 --> 00:45:02,560
with heart pay first.

656
00:45:11,040 --> 00:45:15,320
Then I'll keep this heart.

657
00:45:27,720 --> 00:45:29,640
That was a smooth move, young tiger!

658
00:45:30,240 --> 00:45:31,640
Don't tease him, or the plan will fail.

659
00:45:32,240 --> 00:45:35,400
Sorry. I've never seen this side of him.
I'm not used to it.

660
00:45:37,640 --> 00:45:40,200
We're just here to talk business.

661
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:42,200
Do you really have to put on a show
like this?

662
00:45:42,280 --> 00:45:45,520
I just want to make a good impression.

663
00:45:59,280 --> 00:46:00,680
If I actually

664
00:46:01,640 --> 00:46:03,480
end up impressed,

665
00:46:04,480 --> 00:46:05,720
that could be trouble.

666
00:46:22,080 --> 00:46:25,680
Mam, would you like to see
another one of my magic tricks?

667
00:46:27,200 --> 00:46:29,440
Shall we continue the magic at my condo?

668
00:46:32,680 --> 00:46:36,080
Ris, Mam is coming on strong.

669
00:46:36,720 --> 00:46:40,360
Mam, maybe we should talk
about the investment instead.

670
00:46:42,040 --> 00:46:44,440
I'm not in the mood
for work talk right now.

671
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:46,840
We can discuss it later.

672
00:46:50,560 --> 00:46:53,320
Maybe we should talk about it now.

673
00:46:59,160 --> 00:47:01,360
Well then…

674
00:47:01,920 --> 00:47:04,120
Will you invest five million,

675
00:47:04,200 --> 00:47:07,280
ten million, or 100 million?

676
00:47:08,040 --> 00:47:10,120
Sounds like an interesting offer.

677
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:14,440
But could you give me more details?

678
00:47:15,080 --> 00:47:18,920
Also, I need to check with my dad first.

679
00:47:34,880 --> 00:47:35,720
Mam.

680
00:47:38,960 --> 00:47:42,320
Alright then, that's it.

681
00:47:42,400 --> 00:47:45,000
If there's nothing else, I'll be going.

682
00:47:47,800 --> 00:47:49,760
Mam, are you angry with me?

683
00:47:50,840 --> 00:47:52,840
I don't really understand

684
00:47:52,920 --> 00:47:55,720
what you're trying to achieve
by acting like this.

685
00:47:57,000 --> 00:47:58,920
But it's wasting a lot of my time.

686
00:47:59,920 --> 00:48:01,680
As for the business,

687
00:48:01,760 --> 00:48:04,960
you can ask your father first.

688
00:48:05,040 --> 00:48:07,840
If you want more details,

689
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:10,080
just call Peter.

690
00:48:11,760 --> 00:48:13,400
Mam.

691
00:48:15,560 --> 00:48:18,160
<i>Sending a kid as bait won't work.</i>

692
00:48:18,240 --> 00:48:22,080
From what I know about Mam,
I'll tell you this.

693
00:48:22,160 --> 00:48:24,760
The young guys are just snacks.

694
00:48:24,840 --> 00:48:27,520
Fun for a night or two,
then she gets bored.

695
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:29,200
Her real type

696
00:48:29,280 --> 00:48:31,760
is a middle-aged man

697
00:48:32,360 --> 00:48:33,800
who can provide for her. Got it?

698
00:48:34,400 --> 00:48:37,160
Like Kamnan Chang 13 years ago?

699
00:48:37,240 --> 00:48:38,320
Exactly.

700
00:48:38,960 --> 00:48:41,720
Old, rich, generous.

701
00:48:41,800 --> 00:48:45,640
Once she drains their money,
she either runs or kills them.

702
00:48:48,440 --> 00:48:50,600
That's great. I've got a plan.

703
00:48:51,200 --> 00:48:54,040
Has anyone heard
of comparison advertising?

704
00:48:54,120 --> 00:48:56,440
Before you go on, how do you spell it?

705
00:48:57,120 --> 00:48:58,560
What does that mean?

706
00:48:58,640 --> 00:49:01,080
I told you to speak Thai.

707
00:49:01,920 --> 00:49:03,880
It's a sales psychology technique

708
00:49:04,520 --> 00:49:07,920
that shows our product
is better than the competitor's.

709
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:11,560
This makes it easier
for people to buy from us.

710
00:49:14,040 --> 00:49:15,040
I still don't get it.

711
00:49:15,760 --> 00:49:19,400
Anyway, we're still sending
Mungkorn as bait.

712
00:49:19,480 --> 00:49:22,920
But he has to disappoint Mam.

713
00:49:23,920 --> 00:49:24,840
Disappoint her?

714
00:49:27,120 --> 00:49:30,600
When Mam is disappointed,
her expectations drop.

715
00:49:30,680 --> 00:49:32,360
After that,

716
00:49:32,440 --> 00:49:35,200
we'll send her a better bait
to choose from.

717
00:49:58,400 --> 00:50:00,280
<i>It's like flirting</i>
<i>with a heartbroken woman.</i>

718
00:50:00,360 --> 00:50:02,920
<i>She'll be easier to win over</i>
<i>than when she's happy.</i>

719
00:50:03,000 --> 00:50:05,360
<i>How's that? Can you picture it now?</i>

720
00:50:05,440 --> 00:50:07,600
Wait a moment, sir. I need to check first.

721
00:50:08,720 --> 00:50:12,120
I told you already.
When we're outside, don't call me sir.

722
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:13,760
This isn't Rome.

723
00:50:15,240 --> 00:50:17,560
-Sorry. I forgot myself.
-Go wait in the car for now.

724
00:50:18,600 --> 00:50:19,720
Yes.

725
00:50:32,680 --> 00:50:35,040
Sorry, the bar is closed.

726
00:50:42,440 --> 00:50:45,880
If you don't mind, you can have mine.

727
00:50:46,640 --> 00:50:48,280
I already paid for this bottle,

728
00:50:48,800 --> 00:50:50,320
but I can't finish it.

729
00:50:50,400 --> 00:50:51,400
It's yours.

730
00:50:52,080 --> 00:50:53,120
Are you sure?

731
00:50:54,360 --> 00:50:55,200
It's fine.

732
00:51:18,040 --> 00:51:20,840
Looks like you picked up
something from this man.

733
00:51:27,400 --> 00:51:28,720
That's my ring.

734
00:51:31,360 --> 00:51:32,280
Mam!

735
00:51:32,800 --> 00:51:33,840
You again!

736
00:51:35,360 --> 00:51:39,160
This is the second time
you've committed a crime in front of me.

737
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:41,040
Do you want me to call the police?

738
00:51:41,120 --> 00:51:42,280
Call the police?

739
00:51:42,360 --> 00:51:44,160
Want me to do it now?

740
00:51:46,480 --> 00:51:47,720
I never thought

741
00:51:48,640 --> 00:51:50,640
you could sink this low.

742
00:52:02,040 --> 00:52:03,640
Thank you so much.

743
00:52:04,840 --> 00:52:08,600
Do you know how important
this ring is to me?

744
00:52:08,680 --> 00:52:09,680
Sir!

745
00:52:10,600 --> 00:52:11,440
Something just happened!

746
00:52:11,520 --> 00:52:13,560
I told you, don't call me sir. What is it?

747
00:52:14,200 --> 00:52:17,360
The Sheikh needs to fly back to Abu Dhabi.
The meeting's been moved up.

748
00:52:22,760 --> 00:52:24,440
I have to leave now.

749
00:52:25,040 --> 00:52:26,520
Here's my card.

750
00:52:26,600 --> 00:52:30,040
I'd love the chance
to take you out to dinner sometime.

751
00:52:30,920 --> 00:52:33,520
Sure. Hope your meeting goes smoothly.

752
00:52:45,000 --> 00:52:47,160
Anderson Scott Roma,

753
00:52:47,240 --> 00:52:50,280
the president
of an Italian diamond company?

754
00:53:00,520 --> 00:53:03,080
I still don't know your name. What is it?

755
00:53:05,280 --> 00:53:06,320
Mam.

756
00:53:07,800 --> 00:53:08,880
Mam.

757
00:53:09,840 --> 00:53:11,600
Nice to meet you.

758
00:53:25,720 --> 00:53:27,280
He played that perfectly.

759
00:53:27,880 --> 00:53:30,240
I think Mam's already fallen for him.

760
00:53:34,960 --> 00:53:38,240
That damn Mam!
How could she say I've sunk this low?

761
00:53:39,560 --> 00:53:40,400
Hong.

762
00:53:43,680 --> 00:53:45,920
Hey, Hong!

763
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:50,080
I never thought your life
could sink this low.

764
00:53:50,160 --> 00:53:51,680
Don't rub it in!

765
00:53:51,760 --> 00:53:52,800
Yes, sis.

766
00:53:53,520 --> 00:53:54,800
Hong.

767
00:53:54,880 --> 00:53:55,800
I'm sorry.

768
00:53:55,880 --> 00:53:57,680
You too!

769
00:53:57,760 --> 00:53:59,120
Planning to call the police?

770
00:53:59,200 --> 00:54:01,520
I truly am sorry. At the moment,

771
00:54:01,600 --> 00:54:03,280
I got carried away.

772
00:54:03,360 --> 00:54:07,080
Man, carried away?
When you were saying goodbye,

773
00:54:07,160 --> 00:54:09,080
you were holding her hand and kissing it!

774
00:54:09,160 --> 00:54:12,120
Next time, maybe more
than just a hand kiss.

775
00:54:12,200 --> 00:54:14,000
Yak, you're quick on the draw.

776
00:54:14,080 --> 00:54:15,960
Hong, he's nothing like me.

777
00:54:16,040 --> 00:54:18,120
I'm loyal to just one.

778
00:54:19,080 --> 00:54:20,840
-Whoa, you bastard!
-Why?

779
00:54:20,920 --> 00:54:23,400
You burned the house!
My best friend backstabbed me!

780
00:54:23,480 --> 00:54:24,800
-Why?
-You went this far?

781
00:54:24,880 --> 00:54:26,920
-Yeah!
-You really enjoyed that!

782
00:54:27,000 --> 00:54:28,440
Here's my declaration.

783
00:54:28,520 --> 00:54:31,680
If what I did in this plan

784
00:54:31,760 --> 00:54:33,640
ends my relationship with Hong,

785
00:54:34,280 --> 00:54:36,840
I give up. I'm done. No more.

786
00:54:36,920 --> 00:54:38,800
Hey, bro. No way.

787
00:54:38,880 --> 00:54:42,120
You can't just quit like that.
I'm picturing you with Mam.

788
00:54:42,200 --> 00:54:44,840
None of your business,
or I'll snap at you!

789
00:54:46,800 --> 00:54:50,880
No quitting until I see Mam go to hell.

790
00:54:51,480 --> 00:54:54,640
Okay. Let's keep going.

791
00:55:01,000 --> 00:55:03,320
The first plan seems to have gone well.

792
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:04,640
Yes.

793
00:55:05,760 --> 00:55:09,240
But the hard part comes after this.

794
00:55:14,120 --> 00:55:16,320
Hello. Welcome inside.

795
00:55:17,400 --> 00:55:20,200
Welcome to our family.

796
00:55:20,280 --> 00:55:22,480
We'll get rich together.

797
00:55:22,560 --> 00:55:25,680
Rich! Rich! Rich!

798
00:55:25,760 --> 00:55:27,880
Please register this way.

799
00:55:27,960 --> 00:55:29,720
Welcome inside.

800
00:55:29,800 --> 00:55:31,080
Right this way.

801
00:55:31,160 --> 00:55:32,960
Please come in.

802
00:55:33,040 --> 00:55:33,960
Look at them.

803
00:55:34,560 --> 00:55:36,720
-They're smiling, happy.
-Please register this way.

804
00:55:36,800 --> 00:55:39,520
Don't they realize
they're about to be scammed?

805
00:55:40,680 --> 00:55:42,120
All because of greed, right, Ris?

806
00:55:46,400 --> 00:55:49,200
<i>If that day I hadn't stolen Mam's money,</i>

807
00:55:49,280 --> 00:55:51,640
I probably wouldn't have survived
to see today.

808
00:55:51,720 --> 00:55:54,560
I really have to thank my greed that day.

809
00:55:56,360 --> 00:55:58,400
But a loved one turning into an enemy

810
00:55:59,040 --> 00:56:01,200
is also because of greed.

811
00:56:02,160 --> 00:56:03,480
You really think so?

812
00:56:03,560 --> 00:56:06,120
Of course. If you were mindful

813
00:56:06,200 --> 00:56:08,840
and not blinded by greed, couldn't you see

814
00:56:08,920 --> 00:56:10,480
they're just selling a dream?

815
00:56:10,560 --> 00:56:14,280
Who would believe
a small investment gives huge returns?

816
00:56:14,360 --> 00:56:15,800
Totally crazy.

817
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:18,480
<i>Everything we've done so far,</i>

818
00:56:18,560 --> 00:56:20,920
<i>it's to help people Mam has scammed.</i>

819
00:56:21,000 --> 00:56:23,120
<i>If we can take down Mam's pyramid scheme,</i>

820
00:56:23,200 --> 00:56:24,880
<i>we can help thousands more.</i>

821
00:56:24,960 --> 00:56:26,960
You have to make Mam

822
00:56:27,040 --> 00:56:29,480
fall for you so hard, she can't think.

823
00:56:29,560 --> 00:56:31,800
I haven't been this happy in a long time.

824
00:56:31,880 --> 00:56:35,320
<i>Looks like our Ms. Mam is totally falling</i>

825
00:56:35,920 --> 00:56:37,760
for Mr. Anderson.

826
00:56:37,840 --> 00:56:41,000
You don't care
if it's a pyramid scheme or anything else.

827
00:56:41,080 --> 00:56:41,920
In that case,

828
00:56:42,000 --> 00:56:44,840
transfer all the money
to my account immediately.

829
00:56:44,920 --> 00:56:46,600
He wanted you to think I betrayed you.

830
00:56:46,680 --> 00:56:47,800
Right, Mr. Anderson?

831
00:56:47,880 --> 00:56:50,960
Wait, no. It's Phayak.

832
00:56:51,040 --> 00:56:52,280
Get rid of him.

833
00:56:52,360 --> 00:56:53,160
Sorry, bro.

834
00:57:45,840 --> 00:57:48,680
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
